</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="734" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="26.[1466,2670,722,1067]" pageId="26" pageNumber="734">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1466,1701,757,790]" pageId="26" pageNumber="734">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Phayre’s Squirrel is described as being particularly active and an able leaper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="734" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[1466,2670,722,1067]" pageId="26" pageNumber="734">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1468,2178,836,869]" pageId="26" pageNumber="734">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
